1.00	Baltic_Tatars	Finnish Tatars	The Tatars of Finland are a Turkic people who espouse the Muslim faith. They number approximately 1000 and form a well-established and homogeneous religious, cultural and linguistic minority. The Tatars are the oldest Muslim minority in Finland and throughout the Nordic countries and the Finnish Islamic Congregation the oldest state-recognized Muslim congregation in the Western world. They have their historical origins in Eastern Europe and their language belongs to the Turkic language family.	
